---
import Base from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import EmailCTA from './EmailCTA.astro';
import { products } from '../data/products';
interface Props { category:string; slug:string; title:string; description:string; heading:string; eyebrow:string; intro:string; definition:string; selectionTitle:string; selectionText:string; }
const { category,slug,title,description,heading,eyebrow,intro,definition,selectionTitle,selectionText }=Astro.props;
const list=products.filter(product=>product.category===category);
const crumbs=[{name:'Home',url:'/'},{name:'Products',url:'/products/'},{name:heading,url:`/products/${slug}/`}];
const schema={'@context':'https://schema.org','@type':'CollectionPage',name:heading,description,url:`https://ankaili.com/products/${slug}/`};
---
<Base title={title} description={description} breadcrumbs={crumbs} schema={schema}>
  <section class="page-hero"><div class="container"><p class="eyebrow">{eyebrow}</p><h1>{heading}</h1><p>{intro}</p></div></section>
  <section class="section"><div class="container"><div class="answer-block">{definition}</div><div class="section-head"><h2>Compare Available Models</h2><p class="lead">Check the measuring range, contact functions, output signal and mounting details for each model.</p></div><div class="grid">{list.map(product=><article class="card"><a href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}><img src={product.image} alt={`${product.model} ${category.toLowerCase()}`} width="800" height="800" loading="lazy"></a><p class="eyebrow">{product.model}</p><h3><a href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}>{product.name}</a></h3><p>{product.summary}</p><a class="arrow" href={`/products/${product.slug}/`}>{product.model} specifications</a></article>)}</div></div></section>
  <section class="section tint"><article class="container prose"><h2>{selectionTitle}</h2><p>{selectionText}</p><h3>Start with the temperature you need to monitor</h3><p>Use an OTI for transformer top-oil temperature. Use a traditional WTI when the project requires simulated winding temperature based on top oil and transformer load. If you need data in a PLC, RTU, SCADA system or remote display, specify Pt100, 4-20 mA or RS485.</p><h3>Check the installation before choosing a model</h3><p>Send the transformer type, existing model, measuring range, contact duty, power supply, capillary length, sensing bulb, thread and mounting dimensions. For a replacement, include clear photos of the nameplate, dial, terminals and installed capillary.</p><h3>Order by the complete model code</h3><p>BWY, BWY2, BWR and BWR2 model suffixes can identify different contacts and outputs. Compare the full code with the latest datasheet, outline drawing and terminal diagram before placing an order.</p><p>For remote signals and wiring, see <a href="/applications/substation-remote-temperature-monitoring/">substation transformer monitoring</a> and the <a href="/blog/transformer-temperature-controller-wiring/">transformer temperature controller wiring guide</a>.</p></article></section>
  <EmailCTA title={`Request ${heading} Datasheet and Quote`} subject={`${heading} manufacturer and supplier inquiry`} />
</Base>
